Question 4¶

Calculating Convolution in Frequency Domain¶

In [2]:
sampling_frequency = 100
t1 = np.arange(0, 50, 1/sampling_frequency)
signal = np.zeros(50 * sampling_frequency)
for n in range(20*sampling_frequency, 30*sampling_frequency):
    signal[n] = 1

plt.plot(t1, signal)
plt.title("Signal")
plt.show()
In [3]:
t2 = np.arange(0, 50, 1/sampling_frequency)
kernel = np.zeros(50 * sampling_frequency)
for n in range(1*sampling_frequency, 2*sampling_frequency):
    kernel[n] = (n/sampling_frequency)-1
for n in range(2*sampling_frequency, 7*sampling_frequency):
    kernel[n] = 1.4 - 0.2*(n/sampling_frequency)

plt.plot(t2, kernel)
plt.xlim([0, 10])
plt.title("Kernel")
plt.show()
In [4]:
convolution = np.convolve(signal, kernel)
t3 = np.arange(0, 50, 1/sampling_frequency)
plt.plot(t3, convolution[:50*sampling_frequency])
plt.title("time-domain Convolution")
plt.show()
In [5]:
signal_fft = sp.fft(signal)
kernel_fft = sp.fft(kernel)
convolved_fft = signal_fft * kernel_fft
convolution = sp.ifft(convolved_fft)

plt.plot(t3, np.real(convolution))
plt.title("Convolution using fft")
plt.show()

Narrow-band Temporal Filtering¶

In [6]:
matdata = sio.loadmat("braindata.mat")
timevec = matdata["timevec"][0]
braindata = matdata["braindata"][0]
sampling_frequency = matdata["srate"][0][0]
signal_length = len(braindata)

plt.plot(timevec, braindata)
plt.title("Brain Data (time domain)")
plt.xlabel("time (sec.)", color="orange")
plt.ylabel(r"voltage ($\mu$V)", color="orange")
plt.show()
In [7]:
braindata_fft = sp.fftshift(sp.fft(braindata))
freqs = sp.fftshift(sp.fftfreq(signal_length, 1/sampling_frequency))

plt.plot(freqs, np.square(np.abs(braindata_fft)/signal_length))
plt.ylim([-20, 500])
plt.title("Power Spectrum")
plt.xlabel("frequency")
plt.show()
In [8]:
filtered_frequency = 0
gaussian_filter = np.exp(-(((freqs - filtered_frequency)/4)**2))
filtered_fft = gaussian_filter * braindata_fft

plt.plot(timevec, np.real(sp.ifft(sp.ifftshift(filtered_fft))))
plt.title("Low-Pass Filtered")
plt.show()
In [9]:
filtered_frequency = 10
gaussian_filter = np.exp(-(((freqs - filtered_frequency)/4)**2))
filtered_fft = gaussian_filter * braindata_fft
plt.plot(timevec, np.real(sp.ifft(sp.ifftshift(filtered_fft))))
plt.title("10Hz Filtered")
plt.show()

2D Image Filtering¶

In [10]:
lenna = np.asarray(plt.imread("Lenna.png"))
print(lenna.shape)
size = lenna.shape[0]

(512, 512, 3)

Low Pass Filtering¶

In [11]:
gray_scale = np.zeros((512, 512))
for i in range(size):
    for j in range(size):
        gray_scale[i][j] = np.average(lenna[i][j])

plt.imshow(gray_scale, cmap='gray')
plt.title("gray scale")
plt.show()
In [12]:
gray_scale_fft = sp.fftshift(sp.fft2(gray_scale))
gray_scale_fft_log_formatted = gray_scale_fft.copy()
for i in range(size):
    for j in range(size):
        if np.abs(gray_scale_fft_log_formatted[i][j]) < 1:
            gray_scale_fft_log_formatted[i][j] = 1

plt.imshow(np.log(np.abs(gray_scale_fft_log_formatted)), cmap='gray')
plt.title("Fourier Transform Spectrum")
plt.show()
In [13]:
x = np.linspace(-30, 30, size, endpoint=False)
gaussian_filter = np.zeros((size, size))

for i in range(size):
    for j in range(size):
        gaussian_filter[i][j] = np.exp(-(x[i]**2 + x[j]**2)/8)

plt.imshow(gaussian_filter, cmap='gray')
plt.title("2D Gaussian Filter")
plt.show()
In [14]:
filtered_gray_scale_fft = gray_scale_fft * gaussian_filter
filtered_fft_log_formatted = filtered_gray_scale_fft.copy()
for i in range(size):
    for j in range(size):
        if np.abs(filtered_fft_log_formatted[i][j]) < 1:
            filtered_fft_log_formatted[i][j] = 1

plt.imshow(np.log(np.abs(filtered_fft_log_formatted)), cmap='gray')
plt.title("Low Pass Filtered Spectrum")
plt.show()
In [15]:
filtered_grayscale = sp.ifft2(sp.ifftshift(filtered_gray_scale_fft))
plt.imshow(np.real(filtered_grayscale), cmap='gray')
plt.title("Low Pass Filtered Image")
plt.show()

High Pass Filtering¶

In [16]:
x = np.linspace(-15, 15, size, endpoint=False)
gaussian_filter = np.zeros((size, size))

for i in range(size):
    for j in range(size):
        gaussian_filter[i][j] = 1 - np.exp(-(x[i]**2 + x[j]**2)/8)

plt.imshow(gaussian_filter, cmap='gray')
plt.title("2D High Pass Gaussian Filter")
plt.show()
In [17]:
